definition.value: GM1 gangliosidosis is a rare lysosomal storage disorder characterized biochemically by deficient beta-galactosidase activity and clinically by a wide range of variable neurovisceral, ophthalmological and dysmorphic features.

Gaucher disease (GD) is a lysosomal storage disorder encompassing three main forms (types 1, 2 and 3), a fetal form and a variant with cardiac involvement (Gaucher disease - ophthalmoplegia - cardiovascular calcification or Gaucher-like disease) (see these terms).
A prion disease characterized by adult onset of memory loss, dementia, ataxia, and pathologic deposition of amyloid-like plaques in the brain.

definition.value: L-Arginine:glycine amidinotransferase (AGAT) deficiency is an autosomal recessive disorder of creatine biosynthesis (see this term) described in 7 patients to date and characterized by a mild to moderate intellectual disability, usually without pyramidal/extrapyramidal and behavioral problems. Early diagnosis and treatment with oral doses of creatine monohydrate supplementation appears successful in the prevention of AGAT deficiency manifestations.
